'''Gregory ("Greg") Ion''' (born [[12 March]] [[1963]]) is a former [[Canada|Canadian]] [[football (soccer)|soccer]] player.

Ion was part of the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canadian team]] that participated in their only [[FIFA World Cup]] to date in [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]]. 

A midfielder, Ion played the 1982 [[NASL]] season with the [[Portland Timbers]] and 1983 with the [[Montreal Manic]].  He played 1984 with the [[Tulsa Roughnecks]], scoring 4 goals in 21 matches.  During the 1980s he also played for the [[Vancouver Whitecaps|Vancouver 86ers]] of the [[Canadian Soccer League]]. He is inducted into the BC Sports Hall of Fame as member of the record setting 86ers[http://www.bcsportshalloffame.com/cgi-bin/search.cgi?team_id=44&searchall=1]. 

Ion played [[Major Soccer League|MISL]] [[indoor soccer]] too during the 1980s, playing in 1984-85 with the [[Los Angeles Lazers]].  He played with the [[Tacoma Stars]] in (at least) the 1991-92 season.

Ion was soccer marketer for [[Adidas]].  He currently runs his own marketing company.[http://www.wweek.com/html2/leada013101.html]  He is also Administrative Director of Club Development with youth soccer club [[Washington Premier Football Club]], in [[Tacoma, Washington]].  He is a USSF A licensed coach.

